p:
Fortes et al. observed in a RCT beneficial hematological and glycaemic effects of dietary supplementation with 
 Agaricus sylvaticus in patients with colorectal cancer after surgery (
 Fortes et al., 2008; 
 Costa Fortes et al., 2010; 
 Costa Fortes and Carvalho Garbi Novaes, 2011). The verum group showed significant within-group reductions of fasting plasma glucose, cholesterol, creatinine, aspartate aminotransferase, alanine aminotransferase, immunoglobulin A, immunoglobulin M, systolic and diastolic blood pressure and an improvement in hematological parameters (e.g., hemoglobin, hematocrit, erythrocytes, iron) after 3 and 6 months of treatment, whereas in the placebo group no significant within-group changes were observed. No effects on weight and body mass index were observed. Between-group differences were not calculated.
